						<summary>

						<p>On a rock near the Śekkaḍippāṟai.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman, who took the head of Vīrapāṇḍya (Āditya II) Year 3: 960 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is ruled between the lines. Records that the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">kō</hi> (the land lord) assigned a plot of three <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land as <hi rend="italic">ērippaṭṭi</hi> (evidently for the maintenance of lake of the village).</p>						

						</summary>
